definitions.definition: A sport common in North America, the Caribbean, and East Asia, in which the object is to strike a ball so that one of a nine-person team can run counter-clockwise among four bases , resulting in the scoring of a run . The team with the most runs after termination of play, usually nine innings , wins.
The ball used to play the sport of baseball.
A variant of poker in which cards with baseball-related values have special significance.
